            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ASEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A tape transport system in start-stop regime for",
                " identification mass-separated nuclides and for",
                " transporting activity to gamma-detector"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".By Authors. The observed yields of neutron-rich",
                "rubidium, indium and cesium isotopes, given as ion per",
                "microCoulomb determined at the exit of the typical",
                "surface-ionization ion sources made in tungsten were",
                "reported on figures.",
                " Target and ion source temperature interval",
                "     2100-2400 Celcius degrees.",
                "     Temperature value 2100 was used for MCNPX code."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
